          "Course Grade\n{RSquared: 0.503 - Model 5}\n\nFinal Exam Score\n{RSquared: 0.459 - Model 5}",
          "-",
          "Adding data from multiple sources seems to improve explanatory performance of the linear models.\n\nCuriously, RSquared does not chance significantly when we use Pre-Course surveys + Clickstream vs Post-Course surveys + Clickstream.\n\nAlso… clickstream behaviour is clearly different from the behavior mentioned that students expected to have in the pre-course survey.",
          "Students overestimante their capacity at the start of the course. \n\nOne idfea would be administer surveys during the course, not before it, so that students can… hipothetically… be familiar with the online system before answering.\n\nAppropriate extraction of clickstream data can improve predictive performance.",
